Our Oct-edition cover star is the OG, the poster boy of content creation, who has been writing, acting, shooting, singing, doing all this, and a lot more - @bhuvan.bam22. He is a dream, an aspiration, the SRK of the Content Creation Industry. Tell us if we are wrong! Online or Offline, he has managed to move people with his presence and left a lasting impression. His journey as a creator is both commendable and inspirational. Having him on the cover, shooting with him made us realize that success doesn't happen overnight. One has to work hard to get it. 

Bhuvan Bam gets candid with Social Ketchup Ed, Mrinil Mathur Rajwani, on building the BB ki Vines Universe; donning multiple hats for Dhindora in front of and behind the camera, and more.

‚Ä™I have a bad habit of taking my health for granted. Scripting is usually stressful n needs patience. It usually takes 8-10 days for me to write down an episode and I often isolate myself from the world which is not a right thing to do. Severe headaches and body pain are normal because you put in a lot of effort to meet the expectations of people. But it's a blessing in disguise.

I felt like sharing this with you because I'm happy today. Happy to share another episode, happy to see so many happy messages and smiling faces. Hence, sharing this picture of myself before & after releasing today's video!‚Ä¨ Chehra chamak utha :) Watch my new episode on YouTube.
